 in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Kirmond was born in 1376, in Kirmond le Mire, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Kenermond, was 27 and her mother, Mrs John Kenermond, was 24. She married Thomas Billesby in 1399, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1422, in Bilsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 46."},"et":{"1376–1422":"1376–1422","1376–1430":"1376–1430","1400–1428":"1400–1428","1417–1459":"1417–1459","1350–Male":"1350–Surnud","1353–Female":"1353–Surnud","1459":"1459","18 March 1417":"18. märts 1417","1400":"1400","1422":"1422","1399":"1399","1376":"1376","1353":"1353","1430":"1430","1350":"1350","1417":"1417","1428":"1428","Kirmond Le Mire, Lincolnshire, England":"Kirmond le Mire, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bilsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Bilsby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bilsby, East Lindsey, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bilsby, Lincolnshire, England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Bilesby, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1376–1422":"1376–1422","1376–1430":"1376–1430","1400–1428":"1400–1428","1417–1459":"1417–1459","1350–Male":"1350–Kuollut","1353–Female":"1353–Kuollut","1459":"1459","18 March 1417":"18. maaliskuuta 1417","1400":"1400","1422":"1422","1399":"1399","1376":"1376","1353":"1353","1430":"1430","1350":"1350","1417":"1417","1428":"1428","Kirmond Le Mire, Lincolnshire, England":"Kirmond le Mire, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bilsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Bilsby, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bilsby, East Lindsey, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bilsby, Lincolnshire, England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Bilesby, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshi